INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '91b244c9-d1a1-4bac-8385-e54a7e4380de',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Astro TypeScript — Typed Route Params, Content Schemas, and Zod Search Params$escape$,
  $escape$Astro's type safety story is strongest when you combine `getStaticPaths`, `astro:content` schema inference, and Zod-validated search params.

Route params get their types automatically from `getStaticPaths` — Astro infers `Astro.params` to match exactly what you return. In `[slug].astro`, the moment `getStaticPaths` returns `{ params: { slug: post.slug } }`, `Astro.params.slug` is typed as `string` without casting.

For Content Layer schemas (Astro 5+), define your collection in `src/content.config.ts` via `defineCollection({ loader: glob(...), schema: z.object({...}) })`. Entries are then fully typed through `getCollection` and `getEntry` — no manual type assertions needed.

Search params are the weakest link — `Astro.url.searchParams` returns raw strings. Parse them with Zod at the top of the frontmatter block using `safeParse(Object.fromEntries(...))`. `z.coerce.number()` handles numeric query strings cleanly, and `.default()` eliminates optional chaining downstream.

This three-layer approach — inferred route types, schema-driven content types, Zod-parsed search params — gives you end-to-end type safety across every Astro page without a separate type file.$escape$,
  $escape$// src/pages/docs/[slug].astro
---
import { z } from 'astro/zod';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  const posts = await getCollection('docs');
  return posts.map(post => ({ params: { slug: post.slug } }));
}

const searchSchema = z.object({
  tab: z.enum(['overview', 'api', 'examples']).default('overview'),
  version: z.coerce.number().optional(),
});

const { slug } = Astro.params; // inferred as string
const { tab, version } = searchSchema.parse(
  Object.fromEntries(Astro.url.searchParams)
);
---$escape$,
