INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '390414ae-f46d-4bd2-a9e1-c0dd9fc00f42',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Astro Global UI — Layout-Level Toasts & Modals with transition:persist$escape$,
  $escape$Astro's layout system paired with View Transitions and `transition:persist` is the right primitive for global UI shells. Place interactive islands — Toast, Modal, PageLoader — directly in your base layout and annotate them with `transition:persist`. Astro will skip tearing down and remounting those islands between client-side navigations, preserving component state across route changes.

For shared state, reach for `nanostores`. Define a `$toast` atom in a shared module; any island on any page can write to it without prop drilling or React context. The Toast island reads `$toast` reactively and renders independently of the page content beneath it.

Loading UI follows the same pattern: a `<PageLoader />` island with `transition:persist` listens to `astro:before-preparation` (navigation start) and `astro:page-load` (navigation complete) from the View Transitions event lifecycle to drive a progress indicator. No router wrapper needed — Astro dispatches these events on `document` automatically.

This is cleaner than framework-level providers: the Astro layout *is* the shell, `transition:persist` makes it sticky, and nanostores handle cross-island communication.$escape$,
  $escape$---
// src/layouts/Base.astro
import { ViewTransitions } from 'astro:transitions';
import Toast from '@/islands/Toast';
import PageLoader from '@/islands/PageLoader';
---
<html lang="en">
  <head><ViewTransitions /></head>
  <body>
    <PageLoader client:load transition:persist="page-loader" />
    <Toast client:load transition:persist="global-toast" />
    <slot />
  </body>
</html>$escape$,
  $escape$javascript$escape$,
